CHANGELOG
=========

This file follows Keep a Changelog (https://keepachangelog.com/) and
SemVer with the relaxation declared in docs/PLAN.md §12 decision 12:
v0.x is unstable; v1.0.0 freezes the public API.

## v0.1.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 0 + Tier 1: production-grade synchronous client)

### Added — Tier 0 (security remediation)

- Removed legacy `gorfc/sapnwrfc.ini` containing real-looking SAP
  credentials and corporate hostnames in `*.wdf.sap.corp`.
- Replaced hardcoded credentials in `gorfc/gorfc_test.go` and
  `example/hello_gorfc.go` with `GORFC_TEST_*` env-var lookups; the
  legacy integration tests are now opt-in.
- New `.gitignore` patterns: `sapnwrfc.ini`, `**/sapnwrfc.ini`,
  `*.pse`, `**/sec/`, `nwrfcsdk/`, `sapcrypto/`.
- New `gorfc/sapnwrfc.ini.example` placeholder profile (DIRECT, LB,
  SNC variants).
- New `docs/SECURITY.md` v0: never-commit list, runtime credential
  handling, redaction layers, trace control, license boundary,
  historical-exposure note.
- New `.github/workflows/secret-scan.yml` running gitleaks on every
  push and PR.
- Tightened `gorfc/gorfc.go:1` build tag from
  `(linux && cgo) || (amd64 && cgo) || (darwin && cgo)` (matches any
  amd64 GOOS!) to `(linux || darwin || windows) && cgo`. Added
  `&& !nwrfc_nosdk` so the legacy package is excluded under that tag.
- Fixed `defer C.free` capture-before-assignment leak in
  `gorfc/gorfc.go:fillVariable`. The previous code captured nil
  pointers at defer-time, leaking every fill_variable allocation per
  RFC call.
- New `docs/FEATURE_MATRIX.md`, `docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md`,
  `docs/ROADMAP.md` indices over PLAN.md.

### Added — Tier 1 (core revival)

- New module path `github.com/cjordaoc/gorfc` (community-owned;
  upstream `github.com/sap/gorfc` is archived). go.mod bumped to
  `go 1.23 + toolchain go1.25.0`. testify bumped to v1.10.0.
- New `internal/backend` package: Backend interface, Params (with
  `slog.LogValuer` redaction over SensitiveKeys), CallParams,
  InvokeOptions, Direction bitmask, Version + AtLeast,
  Capabilities, Attributes, FunctionDescriptor, RFCType enum, Date,
  Time, 17 Categorys, SDKError + SDKErrorInfo + Group constants.
- New `internal/sdkbackend` package: cgo bindings over the SAP
  NetWeaver RFC SDK. Files: backend_sdk.go (registry + dispatch),
  cgo_directives.go (per-OS CFLAGS/LDFLAGS plus paired
  goMallocU/goFreeU/goStrlenU/goSetParamActive C helpers),
  ucs.go (RfcUTF8ToSAPUC/RfcSAPUCToUTF8 with leak-free fillString),
  conn.go (Open/Close/Ping/Reset/Attributes), describe.go
  (RfcGetFunctionDesc + recursive type/field walk), invoke.go
  (RfcCreateFunction + fill + RfcInvoke with ctx-cancel watcher
  goroutine + wrap + RfcDestroyFunction), fill.go (Go → ABAP),
  wrap.go (ABAP → Go), errors.go (RFC_ERROR_INFO → backend.SDKError),
  version.go (RfcGetVersion + Capabilities thresholds).
- New `internal/nosdkbackend` package: SDK-free stub. Every method
  returns wrapped backend.ErrUnavailable; nwrfc.mapBackendError
  translates to *SDKUnavailableError.
- New `internal/ucs2` package: UCS-2/UTF-16LE ↔ UTF-8 in pure Go
  (Encode/Decode/EncodeNullTerminated/RStrip/CountCodeUnits).
  Validates and rejects invalid UTF-8 (ErrInvalidUTF8) and unpaired
  surrogates (ErrInvalidUTF16). Fuzz tested.
- New `internal/timeext` package: ABAP DATS/TIMS/UTCLONG parsers
  and formatters in pure Go. Closes upstream silent-zero-date bug
  with explicit ErrZeroDate / ErrZeroTime sentinels. Strict and
  AllowZero options. Fuzz tested.
- New `internal/bcd` package: BCD/DECF16/DECF34 string normalization,
  precision/scale enforcement, signed-zero canonicalization, big.Rat
  formatting helper for codegen.
- New public `nwrfc` package:
  - `Conn` lifecycle: Open / OpenDest / Close (idempotent) / Ping /
    Reset / Attributes / Alive / Backend.
  - `Params` typed struct with redacting LogValue and pre-flight
    validate() that produces *ConfigError.
  - 16-type error hierarchy plus 16 category sentinels and 4 domain
    sentinels (ErrZeroDate, ErrZeroTime, ErrUnknownType,
    ErrConnClosed). Each implements slog.LogValuer with redaction.
  - `Call(ctx, conn, fn, in, out, opts...)` typed marshaling with
    `rfc:"NAME,omitempty"` struct tags, anonymous-field flattening,
    map / pointer / nested struct / slice support. `CallMap` is the
    dynamic-shape sibling.
  - `Pool` with channel-based waiter handoff, LIFO idle stack,
    IdleTimeout / MaxLifetime / AcquireTimeout / AfterAcquire hooks,
    Stats() snapshot, Do() acquire-call-release sandwich with
    discard-on-panic. 16-goroutine race-detector test.
  - `Session` with Commit/Rollback over BAPI_TRANSACTION_COMMIT /
    BAPI_TRANSACTION_ROLLBACK + RfcResetServerContext.
  - `EnsureSDK()`, `SDKVersion()`, `Capabilities()` for runtime
    capability checks. Capability-extension wrappers
    `SetTraceLevel/SetTraceDir/LanguageISOToSAP/LanguageSAPToISO/
    LoadCryptoLibrary/SetIniPath/ReloadIniFile`.
  - WebSocket RFC + crypto loader parameters surfaced via Params.
  - Auto-registration via `nwrfc/register_sdk.go` (cgo) /
    `nwrfc/register_nosdk.go` (no-SDK) blank imports.
- New documentation: `docs/INSTALL.md`, `docs/BUILD.md`,
  `docs/CONFIGURATION.md`, `docs/ERRORS.md`. The existing
  `docs/SECURITY.md` is referenced by all four.

### Changed — breaking from upstream `github.com/sap/gorfc`

- Module path: `github.com/sap/gorfc` → `github.com/cjordaoc/gorfc`.
  Importers update the import path; the new public API lives in the
  `nwrfc/` subpackage. The legacy `gorfc/` package is preserved
  one-version for migration.
- Date/time policy: ABAP "00000000"/"000000" no longer silently maps
  to a zero `time.Time`. Use `nwrfc.CallOptions{AllowZeroDate: true}`
  to opt back in.
- Error shape: previously `*RfcError` and `*GoRfcError`. Now 16
  typed structs in `nwrfc/`. Branch via `errors.Is` sentinels or
  `errors.As` concrete types.

### Fixed

- Memory leak in legacy `fillVariable` (defer evaluating its
  argument at defer-time on a then-nil pointer). Both the legacy
  package and the new internal/sdkbackend get the paired-allocator
  fix.
- Build tag falsely allowed compile on any amd64 GOOS, including
  unsupported BSDs. Now restricted to linux/darwin/windows + cgo.
- Committed credentials.

### Security

- See docs/SECURITY.md §8 for the historical exposure note (real
  credentials previously committed in upstream history).

## Pre-revival (upstream history)

0.2.0 (2020-06-09)
------------------
- ABAP datatypes support completed, added: RFC_DECF16, RFC_DECF34, RFC_UTCLONG
- Error handling extended with GoRfc error type
- RFCTYPE_XSTRING wrap fix, fixed cLen replaced by variable strLen
- ABAP input parameters check extended, covering:
  - Passing non-array to TABLE parameter
  - Datatypes unit tests
- Raise an error if RFM call requested over closed connection

0.1.0 (2020-05-04)
------------------
- Darwin support
- New connection parameters added, type changed to map
- New connection attributes added, type changed to map
- Table parameter accepts also array of variables
- ABAP datatypes conversions fixed:
    - Bytes: RFCTYPE_BYTE, RFCTYPE_XSTRING
    - BCD: RFCTYPE_BCD
- ABAP INT8 type added: RFCTYPE_INT8

0.0.1 (2016-02-01)
------------------
- Initial release
